ental Methods and Materials)','Traditional and contemporary concepts. Image-making using various materials and approaches (representation and abstraction). (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(148,'ART 207B','Drawing and Painting (Experimental Methods and Materials)','Traditional and contemporary concepts. Image-making using various materials and approaches (representation and abstraction). (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(149,'ART 216A','Beginning Sculpture','Creative use of wood and metal, power equipment and hand tools. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(150,'ART 216B','Beginning Sculpture','Creative use of wood and metal, power equipment and hand tools. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(151,'ART 223A','Lettering and Typography','History, design and use of letter forms; the rendering and use of hand-lettered forms. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(152,'ART 223B','Lettering and Typography','History, design and use of letter forms; techniques for rough and comprehensive layouts and introduction to computer graphics. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(153,'ART 223C','Typography into Graphic Design','Technology and its application to typographic and graphic design solutions. Conceptual understanding of current technology as medium and tool in the creative process. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(154,'ART 224','Introduction to Glass','A survey of glass working techniques in glass blowing, hot glass casting, kiln forming, and cold fabrication.',3.0,3.0,0,0),(155,'ART 238','Photo Visual Concepts','Introductory photography course for art majors. Includes the study of photographic vision and design, visual conceptualization and examination of the qualities of light through the use of instant and automatic cameras. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(156,'ART 255','Introduction to 3D Computer Animation','Fundamentals of 3D digital animation production. Introduction to the Maya interface and tools necessary to create 3D assets and explore animation principles. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(157,'ART 263','Perspective Drawing','Introduction to linear perspective systems used to develop and place natural and fabricated forms in space on a two-dimensional surface. Integrated with methods and techniques of rendering light, shadow and reflection on varied subject matter including the human figure. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(158,'ART 300','Writing in the Visual Arts','Principles, practices and objectives of writing in the visual arts. Includes descriptive, analytical and expressive essays; project and grant proposals; artist’s statements; resumes; and professional correspondence. Satisfies the classroom portion of the upper-division writing requirements for art majors.',3.0,3.0,0,0),(159,'ART 306A','Advanced Ceramics','Traditional and contemporary use of ceramic methods, materials and concepts. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(160,'ART 306B','Advanced Ceramics','Traditional and contemporary use of ceramic methods, materials and concepts. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(161,'ART 307A','Drawing and Painting','Concepts, materials and activities in drawing and painting, emphasizing individual skills, ideas, and expression. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(162,'ART 310A','Watercolor','Watercolor media related to varied subject matter and design applications. Includes field trip activity. Provides skills and concepts useful for school art programs. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(163,'ART 311','Foundations of Modern Art','History of painting and sculpture from the French Revolution to the end of the 19th century.',3.0,3.0,0,0),(164,'ART 312','Modern Art','The history of painting, graphic arts and sculpture from late 19th century to World War II.',3.0,3.0,0,0),(165,'ART 315A','Jewelry','Designing and creating jewelry. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(166,'ART 315B','Jewelry','Designing and creating jewelry. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,0),(167,'ART 316A','Sculpture','Sculptural materials and processes. (6 hours activity)',3.0,3.0,0,